						<p>Hello,</p>
<p>Yesterday, it was an important day for one of my customer&#8217;s websites, as she launched a new series of products for summer, expecting many visitors from all around the globe. While she was updating / publishing products, she was purging all caches after a couple of actions, and suddenly the whole website crashed with an internal server error. She wasn&#8217;t able to login as an admin. We checked the resources usage and all the logs at that time, and it wasn&#8217;t a problem by the side of the server, everything was normal. We noticed that something was affecting the htaccess file, re-writing it all the time. We managed to delete and upload a new one, we then connected to the dashboard of the site and deleted the plugin (W3 Total Cache) and everything was fixed. Please, let me know what happened, it was a very very serious issue and we would like to avoid same situations in the future. Otherwise, I&#8217;m afraid we&#8217;ll find another way to add caching to our website.</p>
