						<p>I was searching for this problem and found this post which I think is describing the exact same issue (<a href="https://wordpress.org/support/topic/minify-css-makes-font-missing/" rel="nofollow">https://wordpress.org/support/topic/minify-css-makes-font-missing/</a>)</p>
<p>I don&#8217;t think I changed anything, but all of a sudden all of my fonts were having issues. I think the problem is that they were being stored with relative paths, such as:<br />
<code>src:url(../webfonts/fa-brands-400.eot)</code></p>
<p>Because the minified version of the CSS will be in a completely different location this means that the web browser will try to open <a href="https://mysite.com/wp-content/cache/webfonts/fa-brands-400.eot" rel="nofollow ugc">https://mysite.com/wp-content/cache/webfonts/fa-brands-400.eot</a> which of course it won&#8217;t find.</p>
